explanation:
OS_ObjectIdGetById - Direct callee that performs the initial lookup and may have side effects (e.g. starting transactions, modifying global object state, populating the token). Necessary to know whether removing the call or its effects would change program behavior.

OS_MutSemDelete_Impl - Direct callee that performs the actual semaphore deletion work. Must be inspected to determine whether the call produces externally observable side effects (resource state changes) so its execution is not dead.

OS_ObjectIndexFromToken - Direct callee of OS_MutSemDelete_Impl (from the static call graph). Its behavior may produce side effects or be required for the deletion; relevant when determining whether the higher-level call chain has observable effects.

OS_ObjectIdFinalizeDelete - Direct callee that finalizes the delete operation and may perform cleanup, notifications, or transaction completion. It overwrites return_code; understanding its side effects is essential to decide if the preceding assignment/operation is redundant (dead) or required.

OS_ObjectIdTransactionFinish - Callee of OS_ObjectIdFinalizeDelete per the call graph; may perform transaction completion with observable effects. Needed to see if FinalizeDelete's observable behavior depends on its input and whether earlier operations matter.

OS_NotifyEvent - Callee of OS_ObjectIdFinalizeDelete; may trigger externally visible notifications/events. Required to determine whether FinalizeDelete (and thus the surrounding code) has observable effects.

OS_ObjectIdTransactionInit - Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; may initialize transaction state (side effects) that matter to program behavior and therefore to dead-code determination.

OS_ObjectIdToArrayIndex - Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; may perform conversions or checks that affect state or error return values; required to fully understand GetById effects.

OS_ObjectIdConvertToken - Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; shapes the token passed into subsequent calls. Needed to see whether token-related operations are observable.

OS_ObjectIdTransactionCancel - Callee of OS_ObjectIdGetById; may undo or roll back state on failure; needed to reason about whether skipping calls changes global state.

OS_LOCK_MODE_EXCLUSIVE - Macro/enum value passed to OS_ObjectIdGetById; needed to know semantics of the lookup (exclusive vs shared) because that affects side effects like locking and thus whether the call is dead.

LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE - Macro/enum identifying the object type; needed to understand GetById semantics and whether the lookup triggers type-specific side effects.

OS_SUCCESS - Return-code constant tested by the target function; required to interpret the control flow and determine if certain branches are ever taken or always taken (which affects dead code analysis).

OS_object_token_t - Type of the token used/modified by the callees; needed to know whether its initialization/assignment has observable effects beyond this function (aliasing, global state) and whether operations on it are dead.

osal_id_t - Type of sem_id parameter; needed to know whether passing this id causes implicit conversions or validations with observable side effects (and to fully understand GetById behavior).
